            <h1>User &amp; Portal Permissions Management</h1>
            <h2>User Management</h2>
            <p>This document introduces the user management features of the WSO2 Gadget
                Server:
            </p>

            <h3>Administrator Actions</h3>

            <p>All
the use management operations are only available for the Gadget Server
administrator. The administrator can login with the default admin
username and navigate to the user management area to carry out
administrative tasks. </p>

            <h3>Managing Users
                <br />
            </h3>

            <p>All user management functions require administrative privileges and are provided from
                the 'User Management' page.
            </p>

            <h3>Add User</h3>

            <p>New users can be added to the Gadget server via
                <strong>Home &gt; Configure &gt; User Management &gt; Users &gt; Add New User</strong>
                and following the guided process.
                <br />
                <br />
                <img src="images/Add_User.png" alt="Add User" />
                <br />
            </p>

            <h3>Add New User Role</h3>
            <p>Gadget admin can create new user roles with permissions and assign users to them. By default an Admin
                role is created with all permissions for Gadget Server administration.
            </p>
            <p>A newly created role can have privileges such as,</p>
            <ul>
                <li><b>Admin Permissions</b></li>
                <li>Configure </li>
                <li>Login</li>
                <li>Manage</li>
                <li>Monitor</li>
                <li><b>Super Admin Permissions</b></li>
                <li>Configure</li>
                <li>Monitor</li>
		<li>Server Admin</li>
		
            </ul>

            <p>
                <img src="images/Add_Role.png" alt="Add Role" />
            </p>
            <br />
            <br />
            <p>
                <img src="images/permisionset.png" alt="Add Role" />
            </p>
            <br />
            <h2>Portal Permission</h2>
            <p>Permission to the portal for all users can be set in the administration area by the administrator. The
                administrator can allow users to self register and add external gadgets.
            </p>
            <br /><br />
            <p>
                <img src="images/portal_perm.png" alt="Add Role" />
            </p>
